history.text: Hi
Hello back! Rainy day here...good day for a movie! I really like Leonardo DiCaprio's movies...you?
I love Leonardo DiCaprio's movies! What is this movie about?
I just saw "Wolf of Wall Street"...so good!  Jonah Hill's in it, too.  He's such a diverse actor!
I have never seen that one. I really like the movie inception. I thought the concept was amazing.
At first you don't want to like any of the characters...pretty dull...but then you realize why they're so dull and makes you even more intriqued by them.
Wow. What genre is this movie?
It's a Black Comedy...Rob Reiner's in it, too, so there's that!
It got pretty good scores on Rotten Tomatoes.
Wait so does it have Leonardo dicaprio in it as well> It sounds funny. I really like comedies
Yep, Leo...Margot Robbie, too.  Know her?
Yes! I loved her in I Tonya! Wow it sounds interesting. What is the storyline about?

It
's a memoir...a stockbrokers perspective on his career ono Wall Street, and the fraud and corruption he sees.
ooo so the movie is the wolf of wallstreet. I really do need to watch this. I think I can check it out from my local library
Not sure what it's rated...it's got some drug and salicious behavior in it, just so you know.
I see. Yea I'm not too into those types of movies but if it's just a little then it's ok. I don't mind
Pretty interesting to see what really happens in the world of investing...and how careful you have to be with the scammers out there!
I agree. I like investing and finances. I actually wanted to be a financial adviser at one point
Sounds like in this movie, money truely is the root of all evil.  Drugs, divorce, money laundering, FBI investigations.
Martin Scorsese directed it, so you know it's got to be good!
Wow what else did Martin Scorsese direct? Has it won any awards?
Gosh..I'm not sure.  Kyle Chandler's in it, too, so that makes it a winner with me!
It sounds like it's a star studded cast. I can't imagine it not being good.
Leo's character makes $22 million (illegally) in three hours....whoa!
haha I wish I could do that (legally haha) What would you do with $22 million
Arrange a private screening with Leo of his latest movie!  : )   I don't want to spoil the ending of the movie, but it's pretty tense at the end when he tries to get out of trouble!
He's a great actor. I wonder if it's like all this other movies and he ends up with the worse end of the stick :(
well....let's just say he's not a trader anymore!
Always a sad story for Leo. Well I will see if my local library has this to check out.

uid2response.feedback: I did not have a document so I couldn't read that. My partner was engaging and told me all the highlights of the movie. I would like to see it.
